prompts.frontCover:
Flat 2D watercolor painting of a humorous birthday card for a girlfriend. The scene features cartoon/illustrated versions of the couple from the reference photo.

On the left is Lao Lao, an East Asian woman with long, straight dark brown hair, smiling brightly. She is wearing large, round, thin gold-rimmed glasses and a light yellow sundress with a small pink floral pattern.

On the right is Jordan, a man with light-to-medium tan skin and short, thick, spiky dark hair. He has a huge, exaggerated, cheesy grin on his face. He is wearing a simple white t-shirt. Jordan is holding a comically oversized slice of birthday cake with a single lit candle, offering it towards Lao Lao with an eager expression. Lao Lao looks amused but slightly overwhelmed by the giant cake slice.

The background is a soft, simple watercolor wash of light blues and sandy yellows, suggesting the beach setting from the photo but keeping the focus on the characters. The overall style is lighthearted, with soft flowing colors, visible brush strokes, and organic paint bleeds on a textured paper surface.

Centered on the card, in a beautiful, readable, and elegant handwritten cursive script, is the text: "Happy Birthday, Lao Lao! I love you more than cake (and that's saying a lot)."

- Reference photos provided for character creation
- Characters should only appear on the front cover
- Transform real people into artistic cartoon/illustrated versions matching the style
- Maintain recognizable features while adapting to the artistic style
